				\begin{document}$$\varepsilon_{i,j,k,l,m} = pIC_{50i,j,k,l,m} - {\text{mean}}(pIC_{50i,j,k,l} )$$\end{document}. These errors are assumed to (1) be mutually independent, (2) have zero expectation value, and (3) have constant variance.

To compare the performance of (1) the most predictive ConvNet for each data set and replication, (2) RF and (3) DNN models trained on Morgan fingerprints, and (4) the Ensemble models generated by averaging the predictions of the RF and ConvNet models, we also used a linear model with two factors, namely Data set and Model. In this case, we only considered the results of the ConvNet architecture leading to the lowest RMSE value on the test set for each data set and replication.2pIC50=Dataseti+Modelj+Dataset∗Modeli,j+μ0+εi,j,ki∈1,…,Ndatasets=33;j∈1,…,Nmodels=4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
